# Reduced-sample Table 1 + Figure 4 replication.
#
# Reduced-sample design:
# Initial training:   2000-2011
# Initial validation: 2012-2016
# OOS testing:        2017-2021
#
# For each OOS year, the training window expands by one year and the 5-year validation window rolls forward by one year.
#
# Table 1:
# Models are trained, tuned on the rolling validation window, and used to generate OOS stock-level excess return predictions.
#
# Figure 4:
# Variable importance is computed using the same fitted models used for Table 1.
# For each fitted model, each predictor column is set to zero one at a time while holding the fitted model fixed.
# The variable importance score is the decrease in in-sample panel R2.
#
# This is predictor-level VI.  Therefore, raw characteristics, macro interaction terms, and sic2 dummies can all appear in Figure 4 if they are among the top predictors.

